{
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "corpus": "commands",
  "description": "Recorded utterances that contain a spoken command, replayed through the real no-LLM dictation pipeline by `KeyScribe --commands-check corpus/commands`. Each case asserts declaratively: `contains` = substrings that must survive (a control char \\n/\\t, the clipboard value, or a literal proving a command did NOT fire); `absent` = substrings that must be gone (a consumed trigger phrase, or text 'scratch that' removed); `equals` = the whole output (whole-utterance replacement, case-exact); `noLeadingPunct` = value with no clause punctuation before it (the clipboard fold). Matching is case-insensitive except `equals`. Record <id>.wav for each case in your own voice — real voice reproduces the spurious punctuation/casing engines emit far better than TTS; `say` is a quick synthetic smoke that will NOT reproduce fold/empty-segment punctuation. The clipboard VALUE below is inserted by the pipeline, never spoken.",
